## Framework & runtime
- WebdriverIO **9.26.x**, Mocha (bdd), TS via `test/tsconfig.json`. BiDi: `webSocketUrl: true`, ChromeDriver download skipped.
- Product: **learn-webapp**. `baseUrl` defaults to `https://learn.adept.at` (override via `BASE_URL` env or Sauce `--baseUrl=...`).
- Local: Chrome, `waitforTimeout` 10s, Mocha timeout 600000. Sauce: `maxInstances: 5`, Win11, Chrome/Firefox/Edge `latest`.

## Page objects
- `test/pageobjects/`: `page.ts` (base), `login.page.ts`, `adept.video.player.ts` (canonical video/mux abstraction — use its APIs, never reimplement mux indexing).
- Skill chrome: `test/specs/skills/pages/skill.page.ts` (e.g. `closeComments`).
- Video flow APIs all route through `scrollToVideo` + `_activeWrapperId`: `startVideoIndexAndMonitorEvents`, `pauseVideo`, `startVideoWithTranscripts`, `startVideoWithTranscriptsMobile`.

## Selectors
- **Stable**: video wrappers `div[id^="component-"]` are always in the DOM.
- **Lazy / unstable**: `mux-player` instances mount/unmount via IntersectionObserver — never use global `mux-player` count as a readiness signal.
- Transcripts: tab `[role="tab"][aria-label^="Video transcript"]` (production says "transcripts" plural, dev says "transcript" — always anchor with `aria-label^=`); entries `[role="button"][aria-label^="Jump to timestamp"]`.
- Skill chrome: prefer `data-testid` (e.g. `skill-length-and-creation-date`); sidebar close `[aria-label="Close sidebar"]`.
- Mux shadow UI: `clickElementInMuxPlayer` with selectors like `media-play-button`, `media-settings-menu-button`, `media-transcript-button`, `#adept-theatre`.
- **Anti-patterns**: treating the first visible `mux-player` as the Nth video; exact-match on transcript aria-label; brittle absolute XPaths.

## Waits / timing
- Allowed: `browser.waitUntil` with `timeoutMsg` and `interval`; `waitForExist` / `waitForDisplayed` / `waitForClickable` on concrete elements; intentional `browser.pause` only for documented Edge BiDi or login spacing.
- **Banned**: `$('mux-player').waitForExist({ timeout: 120000 })` after login on multi-video skills — wait for component wrappers and let `scrollToVideo` mount the player on demand.
- Skill ready signal: `browser.waitUntil(() => $$('div[id^="component-"]').length > 0, { timeout: 120000, interval: 1000, timeoutMsg: 'No video component wrappers found' })`.
- Edge: expect an extra `browser.pause(1500)` after resolving the mux host; do not strip without repro on Sauce Edge BiDi.

## Auth & test setup
- `LoginPage.login` sets `adept_testing_flag=1` (`setIgnoreCaptchaCookie`) before navigating; verifies via `getIgnoreCaptchaCookie`. BiDi cookie failures fall back to `document.cookie` — keep the fallback.
- After login on skill URLs: best-effort close the comments sidebar via `SkillPage.closeComments` — when `[aria-label="Close sidebar"]` is clickable it can otherwise cover the player.
- Use `BiDiHelper.waitForNavigationComplete()` after `browser.url(...)` for new BiDi-aware navigation.

## Mux / video lifecycle (the distinctive concern)
- learn-webapp keeps only ~2–3 `mux-player` nodes mounted at a time; scrolling triggers IntersectionObserver to mount/unmount.
- `scrollToVideo(index)` is the canonical way to make the Nth video active: scrolls the corresponding `#component-…` wrapper into view, sets `_activeWrapperId`, then resolves mux via `getElementById(wrapperId).querySelector('mux-player')` rather than `document.querySelector('mux-player')`.
- Tests targeting high-index videos (e.g. the 4th) must use `scrollToVideo(3)` semantics — never assume 4 mux nodes coexist.
- Playback assertions go through `startVideoIndexAndMonitorEvents`, which enforces `maxBufferingOccurrences` / `maxEventOccurrences`. Don't bypass.

## Common pitfalls
- Transcript timeouts often trace back to a broken **setup** wait (mux globally instead of component wrappers), not the transcript poll itself.
- Don't introduce blanket `browser.pause` to "fix" flake — replace with `waitUntil` + `timeoutMsg`.
